# Nearco II (Remake) - La perdición de la Ninfa - Vr Offline
# Jhames, 2011 (ASL 500, Spanish). No published walkthrough exists — derived
# from game source (game.aslx). Ending: entering the Playa calls finish
# ("FELICIDADES HAS TERMINADO NEARCO 2") after the nymph opens Aries' north
# passage. Chain: meet the ninfa in the forest (she only appears on the
# SECOND visit — the room's exit script moves her in when you leave), answer
# `di ninfa si` → star-labyrinth passage; in Cancer (Alexander the Great's
# natal house — born 356 BC) say `nerea 356` → Zeus drops the pandigital
# pergamino, and `di zeus serpiente` → the anti-snake spray; tell the blind
# mathematician `di viejo 1036957284` (the magic square's missing pandigital
# number) → cemetery path opens; `rocia serpiente con antiserpientes` clears
# the bridge road; push the spherical Indiana-Jones roca twice (cornisa →
# cornisa1 → over the cliff onto the tomb below, smashing the losa — this
# works BEFORE ever visiting the cemetery); x the opened tumba, whose look
# script parks its tail on a SYNCHRONOUS `play sound ("craneo.mp3", true,
# false)` — the skull only materialises when the next engine Wait pumps the
# parked continuation (The Tree precedent), which here is the comic cíclope
# encounter (armed by the first cemetery visit, fires WaitForKeyPress on the
# way back through Camino Noroeste); return and x the cráneo (its numbered-
# bones cipher spells the dead lover's name); with the skull examined the
# ninfa ambushes you in Aries — `di ninfa teofet` names her beloved TEOFET
# and opens the way north to the beach. The game ships a malformed
# DefaultPull dynamictemplate ("No puedes tirar de eso".") that legacy Quest
# tolerated — the oracle now registers it lazily (patch_questviva.py §3).
# No score; no RNG; music/pictures are display-only.
